## 2026-03-28 - Toast stacking system: queue multiple toasts vertically instead of overlapping
- Replaced single-toast-at-a-time system with a proper stacking queue. Previously, success/error/undo toasts were mutually exclusive via conditional priority (`!toastVisible`, `!successToast`). Now multiple toasts render simultaneously in a vertical stack with `gap-1.5`, each with independent auto-dismiss timers and slide-up animation.
- Created `useToastStack` hook that manages a `ToastItem[]` array with `pushSuccess`/`pushError`/`dismiss` ‚Äî replaces the old `useState<string | null>` for success and error toasts.
- Created `ToastStack` component that renders up to 5 visible toasts stacked from bottom, with the undo toast (still managed by `useUndo`) rendered at the base of the stack. Each toast gets an `animate-toast-in` CSS animation (150ms slide-up + fade-in).

